        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 9:03PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 902 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Lisbon, or 8 miles southwest of Salem, moving northwest
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alliance, Louisville, Sebring, Minerva, Hartville, Randolph, Atwater,
Beloit, Deerfield, Limaville, Robertsville, Maple Ridge, Maximo,
Uniontown, and Greentown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
